SavvySpender App Privacy Policy
INTRODUCTION
About Us
SavvySpender Limited ("we"/ "us"/ "our")  offers a mobile application designed to assist savvy shoppers in finding bargains and planning their weekly shopping efficiently to maximise savings. Our app allows users to compare prices across various supermarkets, manage in-store shopping lists, and search for retailer discounts ("the Services").
About Our Privacy Policy
We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data in an open and transparent manner. This privacy policy ("Policy") outlines your rights concerning the processing of your personal data and the basis on which any personal data we collect from you, or that you provide to us, will be processed when you use the Savvy Spender mobile application ("our App").
We do not target or knowingly collect information from children under 16 years of age.
Controller
For the purposes of this Policy, under the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679 ("GDPR") and other applicable laws, we act as the "controller" of the personal data you provide to us.
THE INFORMATION WE COLLECT
We collect and process various types of data for specific purposes:
Information You Give Us:
Your Data: Includes information you provide when using our Site or Services, such as filling in forms or using app features such as adding items to your in-app shopping list. This may include your name, address, email, phone number or age.
Information We Collect About You:
Automatically Collected Information: Each time you use our App, we may automatically collect technical data (like IP addresses, browser types, and login information) and usage data (such as your navigation through our Site/App, products viewed, and interaction details).
Cookies:
Our Site and App may use cookies to enhance your experience and gather statistical information to help improve our services. You can control the use of cookies through your browser settings.
WHAT WE DO WITH YOUR INFORMATION
We use your personal data lawfully, either where necessary for our contractual obligations, for our legitimate interests, or with your consent. The table below describes how we use your data and our legal bases for processing:
