Change of Purpose:
We will only use your personal data for the purposes we collected it for or other compatible purposes. If we need to use your data for an unrelated purpose, we will notify you and explain the legal basis allowing us to do so.
DISCLOSURE OF YOUR INFORMATION
We do not sell your personal data. We may share your data with selected third parties for service performance, analytics, and legal obligations. This includes:
Subsidiaries, business partners, and contractors for service delivery.
Analytics and search engine providers for optimisation.
Legal and regulatory authorities as required.
INTERNATIONAL TRANSFERS
Your personal data may be transferred outside the EEA for processing by our partners or service providers. We ensure such transfers comply with legal requirements and your data remains protected.
SECURITY MEASURES
We implement appropriate measures to protect your data from unauthorised access or disclosure. Our team is trained in data protection, and we have procedures to address potential data breaches.
YOUR PERSONAL DATA AND YOUR RIGHTS
You have various rights under data protection laws, including access, correction, erasure, and objection to processing. You can exercise these rights by contacting us.
MARKETING COMMUNICATIONS
We will only send you marketing communications with your consent, and you can opt-out at any time.
CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
We may update this Policy periodically. Significant changes will be communicated to you before they take effect.
QUESTIONS OR COMPLAINTS
If you have any concerns about our use of your personal data, please contact us at:
SavvySpender 24 Loch View, Buncrana Co. Donegal. Email:
office@savvyspender.ie
You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority if you believe we have not complied with data protection laws.
Effective Date of this Policy: 13th March 2024